examples.en: He brought my coat and his.
examples.ru: Он принёс моё и своё пальто.

examples.en: I brought him a book.
I brought my camera along
It brought out his better side.
examples.ru: Это происшествие показало его с лучшей стороны.

examples.en: She is very piggishly brought up.
The sale brought in over $250.
examples.ru: Прибыль от продаж составила более 250 долларов.

examples.en: Mother brought a pretty Poll.
He brought his instruments along.
I was brought up a Catholic.
examples.ru: Я был воспитан в католической вере.

examples.en: It brought the scandal to light.
They brought the water to a boil.
My aunt brought up four children.
His story brought tears to her eyes.
examples.ru: От его рассказа у неё на глаза навернулись слёзы.

examples.en: I was brought up to respect the law.
examples.ru: Меня воспитывали в уважении к закону.

examples.en: The warm sun brought the flowers out.
examples.ru: Цветы распустились под тёплыми лучами солнца.

examples.en: The hunter brought down a deer.
Supplies were brought in by air.
examples.ru: Снабжение осуществлялось по воздуху /воздушным путём, при помощи авиации, авиатранспортом/.

examples.en: Her question brought me up short.
examples.ru: Её вопрос прервал меня на полуслове.

examples.en: The waiter brought drinks on a tray.
The waiter brought the next dish on.
She brought honour to her family.
The jury brought in an acquittal.
The pain brought tears to his eyes.
examples.ru: От боли у него на глазах появились слёзы.

examples.en: The famine brought mass starvation.
examples.ru: Нехватка еды привела к массовому голоду.

examples.en: He brought reproach upon his family.
The team brought honor to the school.
She brought home a carload of books.
examples.ru: Она привезла домой целый вагон книг.

examples.en: Tom has brought out another new book.
The gunners brought down three planes.
The union was brought into submission.
